Superb dining experience. Our server was incredibly friendly and knowledgable, and even spent time explaining a variety of menu options to our curious teenager. Dinner was incredible. My husband and I split a 30oz slab of waygu called a 'tomahawk' It cut like butter. My son's rib-eye was just right. Other party members were extremely happy with their trout and sushi. The family-style sides were excellent. I'm drooling as I write this review... the gorgonzola macaroni and cheese is a must. For dessert, the butter cake. Just get it. Your world will be rocked.

